[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The sovereign "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " showed me this: I saw"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " him making locusts just as the crops planted late"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " were beginning to sprout. (The crops planted late sprout after the royal harvest."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ") "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When they had completely consumed the earth’s vegetation, I said, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“Sovereign "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", forgive Israel!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "How can Jacob survive?"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "He is too weak!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " decided not to do this."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “It will not happen,” the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " said. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The sovereign "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " showed me this: I saw"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the sovereign "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " summoning a shower of fire."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " It consumed the great deep and devoured the fields."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I said, “Sovereign "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", stop! "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "How can Jacob survive?"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "He is too weak!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " decided not to do this."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The sovereign "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " said, “This will not happen either.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He showed me this: I saw"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the sovereign One"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " standing by a tin"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " wall holding tin in his hand. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " said to me, “What do you see, Amos?” I said, “Tin.” The sovereign One then said,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“Look, I am about to place tin among my people Israel. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "I will no longer overlook their sin."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Isaac’s centers of worship"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " will become desolate;"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Israel’s holy places will be in ruins."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "I will attack Jeroboam’s dynasty with the sword.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Amaziah the priest of Bethel"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " sent this message"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to King Jeroboam of Israel: “Amos is conspiring against you in the very heart of the kingdom of Israel!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The land cannot endure all his prophecies."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " As a matter of fact,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Amos is saying this: ‘Jeroboam will die by the sword and Israel will certainly be carried into exile"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " away from its land.’” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Amaziah then said to Amos, “Leave, you visionary!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Run away to the land of Judah! Earn your living"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and prophesy there! "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Don’t prophesy at Bethel"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " any longer, for a royal temple and palace are here!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Amos replied"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to Amaziah, “I was not a prophet by profession."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " No,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I was a herdsman who also took care of"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " sycamore fig trees."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " took me from tending"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " flocks and gave me this commission,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " ‘Go! Prophesy to my people Israel!’ "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So now listen to the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "’s message! You say, ‘Don’t prophesy against Israel! Don’t preach"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " against the family of Isaac!’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Therefore this is what the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " says:"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "‘Your wife will become a prostitute in the streets"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "and your sons and daughters will die violently."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Your land will be given to others"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "and you will die in a foreign"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " land."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Israel will certainly be carried into exile"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " away from its land.’”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]